speech.p:
asked the President of the Board of Trade (1) whether he will make some inquiry through the Food Council or other

channels regarding the official price of flour, with a view to ensuring that the official price is not artificially manipulated to a higher level than the selling price of the day;

(2) what provision has been made to safeguard the official price of flour in all areas throughout the country being manipulated so as to prevent a break in the price of bread which would occur if this price were not manipulated?

asked the Secretary of State for War (1) whether any, and, if so, which, detachment of the

Regular or Territorial Army at camp are supplied with new-laid eggs solely of United Kingdom origin;

(2) whether he will state the amount of the cash allowance from which messing officers buy eggs for the troops; whether it is sufficient to provide the troops with new-laid eggs produced in this country; and whether he will circularise messing officers as to the desirability of, whenever possible, supplying the troops with home-produced foodstuffs?
